    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix missing MMX state cleanup in DFT functions causing x86 compilation failure\n\n### Summary\nThe NR PHY DFT implementation fails to compile on x86 platforms due to missing definitions for `_mm_empty()` and `_m_empty()` macros. These functions are used throughout the DFT library for proper MMX state cleanup but were only defined for ARM architectures.\n\nThe issue was introduced when the DFT library was extended to support larger transform sizes (1296-point and above) but the x86-specific MMX cleanup macros were not properly defined in the tools header.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair1/PHY/TOOLS/tools_defs.h`: Added proper x86 definitions for `_mm_empty()` and `_m_empty()` using inline assembly to execute the `emms` instruction\n- `openair1/PHY/TOOLS/oai_dfts.c`: Fixed trailing semicolon syntax in dft1296 function\n\n### Reproduction\nTo reproduce the issue:\n1. Attempt to build OAI5G on an x86_64 platform with DFT support enabled\n2. Compilation will fail with errors like:\n   ```\n   error: implicit declaration of function '_mm_empty'\n   error: implicit declaration of function '_m_empty'\n   ```\n3. The error occurs in multiple DFT functions including dft1296, dft432, and others that call these cleanup functions\n\nThe fix ensures proper MMX state cleanup on x86 platforms while maintaining existing ARM compatibility.\n"
}